   "source": [
    "## Advanced Lane Finding Project\n",
    "\n",
    "The goals / steps of this project are the following:\n",
    "\n",
    "* ~~Compute the camera calibration matrix and distortion coefficients given a set of chessboard images.~~\n",
    "* ~~Apply a distortion correction to raw images.~~\n",
    "* ~~Use color transforms, gradients, etc., to create a thresholded binary image.~~\n",
    "* ~~Apply a perspective transform to rectify binary image (\"birds-eye view\").~~\n",
    "* ~~Detect lane pixels and fit to find the lane boundary.~~\n",
    "* ~~Determine the curvature of the lane and vehicle position with respect to center.~~\n",
    "* ~~Warp the detected lane boundaries back onto the original image.~~\n",
    "* ~~Output visual display of the lane boundaries and numerical estimation of lane curvature and vehicle position.~~\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compute the camera calibration matrix and distortion coefficients given a set of chessboard images."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import cv2\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from pylab import rcParams\n",
    "from example import *\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "INIT_FIG_SIZE = rcParams['figure.figsize']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# prepare object points, like (0,0,0), (1,0,0), (2,0,0) ....,(6,5,0)\n",
    "objp = np.zeros((6*9,3), np.float32)\n",
    "objp[:,:2] = np.mgrid[0:9,0:6].T.reshape(-1,2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Arrays to store object points and image points from all the images.\n",
    "objpoints = [] # 3d points in real world space\n",
    "imgpoints = [] # 2d points in image plane.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Make a list of calibration images\n",
    "images = glob.glob('../camera_cal/calibration*.jpg')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step through the list and search for chessboard corners\n",
    "for fname in images:\n",
    "    img = cv2.imread(fname)\n",
    "    gray = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Find the chessboard corners\n",
    "    ret, corners = cv2.findChessboardCorners(gray, (9,6),None)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # If found, add object points, image points\n",
    "    if ret == True:\n",
    "        objpoints.append(objp)\n",
    "        imgpoints.append(corners)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Draw and display the corners\n",
    "        img = cv2.drawChessboardCorners(img, (9,6), corners, ret)\n",
    "        #cv2.imshow('img',img)\n",
    "        #cv2.waitKey(500)\n",
    "\n",
    "#cv2.destroyAllWindows()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ret, mtx, dist, rvecs, tvecs = cv2.calibrateCamera(objpoints, imgpoints, gray.shape[::-1], None, None)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Define conversions in x and y from pixels space to meters\n",
    "ym_per_pix = 30/720 # meters per pixel in y dimension\n",
    "xm_per_pix = 3.7 # meters per pixel in x dimension"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Determine the curvature of the lane and vehicle position with respect to center."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Left lane Curvature: 38461.11\tRight lane Curvature: 2805.15\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "y_eval = out_img.shape[0]*ym_per_pix\n",
    "\n",
    "left_curverad = np.round(((1 + (2*left_fit[0]*y_eval + left_fit[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*left_fit[0]),2)\n",
    "right_curverad = np.round(((1 + (2*right_fit[0]*y_eval + right_fit[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*right_fit[0]),2)\n",
    "print('Left lane Curvature: {}\\tRight lane Curvature: {}'.format(left_curverad, right_curverad))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Offset: 0.06\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "left_lane_pos = out_img[out_img.shape[0]//2+100:,:,0].sum(axis=0)[:out_img.shape[1]//2].argmax()\n",
    "right_lane_pos = out_img[out_img.shape[0]//2+100:,:,2].sum(axis=0)[out_img.shape[1]//2:].argmax()+out_img.shape[1]//2\n",
    "center_line = out_img.shape[1]//2\n",
    "offset = np.round(((center_line-left_lane_pos)/(right_lane_pos-left_lane_pos)-0.5)*xm_per_pix,2)\n",
    "print('Offset: {}'.format(offset))"
   ]

    "cv2.putText(dst_lanes, 'Left lane Curvature  :  {}'.format(left_curverad), (50,50), font, 1, (255, 255, 0), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",

    "cv2.putText(dst_lanes, 'Vehicle position      :  {}'.format(offset), (50,130), font, 1, (255, 255, 0), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "plt.imshow(dst_lanes)"
   ]

   },
   "source": [
    "## Final Pipeline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 55,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def process(src):\n",
    "    ### DISTORTION CORRECTION\n",
    "    dst = cv2.undistort(src, mtx, dist)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ### THRESHOLDING USING A STUDENT PROPOSED FILTER\n",
    "    comb_threshold = 255*combined_threshold(dst)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ### PERSPECTIVE TRANSFORM\n",
    "    IMAGE_H = 223\n",
    "    IMAGE_W = 1280\n",
    "\n",
    "    src_p = np.float32([[0, IMAGE_H], [1207, IMAGE_H], [0, 0], [IMAGE_W, 0]])\n",
    "    dst_p = np.float32([[563, IMAGE_H], [711, IMAGE_H], [0, 0], [IMAGE_W, 0]])\n",
    "\n",
    "    #IMAGE_H = 270\n",
    "    #IMAGE_W = 1280\n",
    "    \n",
    "    #src_p = np.float32([[0, IMAGE_H], [1200, IMAGE_H], [0, 0], [IMAGE_W, 0]])\n",
    "    #dst_p = np.float32([[570, IMAGE_H], [690, IMAGE_H], [0, 0], [IMAGE_W, 0]])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    warped_img = warper(comb_threshold[450:(450+IMAGE_H)], src_p, dst_p)[:,550:-550]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        ### LANE DETECTION AND FITTING USING SLIDING WINDOWS\n",
    "        out_img, left_fit, right_fit = fit_polynomial(np.int16(warped_img), 10, 20, 0.001)\n",
    "\n",
    "        ### CALCULATING OFFSET AND RADIUS OF CURVE\n",
    "        y_eval = out_img.shape[0]*ym_per_pix\n",
    "\n",
    "        left_curverad = np.int64(((1 + (2*left_fit[0]*y_eval + left_fit[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*left_fit[0]))\n",
    "        right_curverad = np.int64(((1 + (2*right_fit[0]*y_eval + right_fit[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*right_fit[0]))\n",
    "\n",
    "        left_lane_pos = out_img[out_img.shape[0]//2+100:,:,0].sum(axis=0)[:out_img.shape[1]//2].argmax()\n",
    "        right_lane_pos = out_img[out_img.shape[0]//2+100:,:,2].sum(axis=0)[out_img.shape[1]//2:].argmax()+out_img.shape[1]//2\n",
    "        center_line = out_img.shape[1]//2\n",
    "        offset = np.round(((center_line-left_lane_pos)/(right_lane_pos-left_lane_pos)-0.5)*3.7,2)\n",
    "\n",
    "        ### INVERSE PERSPECTIVE TRANSFORM\n",
    "        #final_img = np.zeros_like(warper(edges[450:(450+IMAGE_H)], src_p, dst_p))\n",
    "\n",
    "        final_img = np.zeros_like(warper(comb_threshold[450:(450+IMAGE_H)], src_p, dst_p))\n",
    "        final_img = np.dstack((final_img,final_img,final_img))\n",
    "        final_img[:,550:-550] = out_img\n",
    "        final_img = warper(final_img, dst_p, src_p)\n",
    "        detection = np.zeros_like(dst)\n",
    "        detection[450:(450+IMAGE_H)] = final_img\n",
    "\n",
    "        ### ADDING DETECTION TO THE UNDISTORTED IMAGE\n",
    "        dst_lanes = cv2.cv2.addWeighted(dst, 1, detection, 0.9, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "        ### ADDING RADIUAL OF CURVATURE AND VEHICLE POSITION TO THE FRAME\n",
    "        font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX\n",
    "        cv2.putText(dst_lanes, 'Left lane Curvature  :  {} (m)'.format(left_curverad), (50,50), font, 1, (255, 255, 0), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "        cv2.putText(dst_lanes, 'Right lane Curvature :  {} (m)'.format(right_curverad), (50,90), font, 1, (255, 255, 0), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "        cv2.putText(dst_lanes, 'Vehicle position      :  {} (m)'.format(offset), (50,130), font, 1, (255, 255, 0), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "\n",
    "        return dst_lanes\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        return dst"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Testing on images"
   ]
